01:35:44.960 --> 01:35:46.960
那我们在十一月就要投入生产
then we'll need the tapes in Smiths by November.

01:35:47.720 --> 01:35:51.400
我的提议是 你来这里写程序
OK. So here's my proposal. Come and write it here.

01:35:52.680 --> 01:35:53.720
-这里？  -对啊
-Here?  -Yeah!

01:35:54.200 --> 01:35:57.480
我们专门为你安排几张桌子 建一个小团队
We'll give you a couple of desks, set up a small team, just for you.

01:35:57.840 --> 01:35:59.640
当然 科林也在附近
And of course Col's on hand.

01:36:00.160 --> 01:36:01.360
你怎么想？
What do you reckon?

01:36:03.240 --> 01:36:04.920
对了 我下周会雇用一个做声卡的
Oh, and hey, I'm hiring this sound chip guy next week,

01:36:05.000 --> 01:36:07.800
所以音乐我们可以解决 全在公司内部做
so music we can take care of. All in-house.

01:36:08.120 --> 01:36:10.200
说吧 你怎么看？
So, come on. What's your answer?

01:36:15.960 --> 01:36:18.400
（1984年7月9日）

01:36:23.360 --> 01:36:24.400
吃早餐吗？
Breakfast?

01:36:25.280 --> 01:36:26.120
潘达什么？
-Your Bander-what?  -Bandersnatch.

01:36:26.960 --> 01:36:29.520
潘达斯奈基 这本书是“选择自己的冒险”
-It's a "Choose Your Own Adventure" book.  -That bloody hound from next door!

01:36:29.600 --> 01:36:30.520
隔壁那条该死的猎犬 真是烦死人了
Be the death of us.

01:36:34.720 --> 01:36:36.360
（朋友  没有未来）

01:36:38.760 --> 01:36:40.080
（塔克软件）

01:36:40.280 --> 01:36:42.000
我们会成为热门产品工厂
We're going to be a hit factory.

01:36:42.080 --> 01:36:45.280
科林·里特曼？太疯狂了 我玩过他所有游戏
Colin Ritman? That's crazy. I've played all of his games.

01:36:45.360 --> 01:36:48.240
看看他这状态 今年赚的钱都够买兰博基尼了
State of him, he's made enough this year to buy a Lamborghini

01:36:48.320 --> 01:36:50.440
但还是抽自己卷的烟
and he still smokes roll-ups.

01:36:55.880 --> 01:36:58.520
-我们之前见过  -没有
-We've met before.  -No.

01:37:01.400 --> 01:37:02.840
我现在在做这个
This is what I'm working on.

01:37:04.360 --> 01:37:07.880
-鼻子跳水  -没错
-Nohzdyve.  -Yeah. That's right.

01:37:07.960 --> 01:37:09.000
（运行）

01:37:14.240 --> 01:37:15.120
可恶
Oh, bollocks.

01:37:15.200 --> 01:37:16.880
-怎么了？  -缓冲区错误
-What's that?  -Buffer error.

01:37:18.760 --> 01:37:22.000
游戏界面超显存了
Those eyeball sprites overshot the video memory.

01:37:23.440 --> 01:37:24.560
你怎么知道
How did you know that?

01:37:25.680 --> 01:37:28.280
-没怎么啊  -我的天 他很优秀吧？
-Just did.  -Bloody hell, he's good, right?

01:37:28.920 --> 01:37:33.320
好了 来说正经事 斯蒂芬有东西要演示给我们看
Anyway, let's get down to business. Stefan's got something to demo for us.

01:37:35.120 --> 01:37:37.720
用游戏杆做选择 有十秒时间
You choose with the joystick. See. You've got ten seconds.

01:37:38.480 --> 01:37:40.840
别崇拜他 他是命运之窃贼
Don't worship him, he's the Thief of Destiny.

01:37:40.920 --> 01:37:43.720
-你读过《潘达斯奈基》？  -杰罗姆·戴维斯 很有远见
-You've read Bandersnatch?  -Jerome F. Davies. Visionary.

01:37:44.040 --> 01:37:46.840
他就是那个发了疯 把老婆脑袋砍掉的家伙？
Was he that bloke who went cuckoo and cut his wife's head off?

01:37:46.920 --> 01:37:48.520
对 大家都倾向于关注这一点
That is what people tend to focus on, yes.

01:37:49.000 --> 01:37:51.280
你是哪个结局？读那本书的时候
Which ending did you get? When you read it.

01:37:51.360 --> 01:37:52.720
-全部结局  -不好意思
-All of them.  -Excuse me.

01:37:55.280 --> 01:37:56.160
（崇拜帕克斯）

01:37:57.080 --> 01:37:59.920
-怎么回事？  -这条路的程序我还没写
-What's happened?  -I haven't programmed that path yet.

01:38:00.400 --> 01:38:02.280
是哦 有很多条路？
Right. So, a lot of paths then?

01:38:02.800 --> 01:38:05.000
对 如果按书里来 就会这样
Well, yes, if it's going to be like the book.

01:38:05.080 --> 01:38:06.680
书里有很多不同的现实
A lot of divergent realities in that book.

01:38:07.320 --> 01:38:10.840
这本书很超前 因为时间是存在的
It was ahead of its time. In as much as time exists.

01:38:12.200 --> 01:38:16.080
好 我的提议是 你来这里写程序
OK. So here's my proposal. Come and write it here.

01:38:17.160 --> 01:38:18.000
这里？
Here?

01:38:18.080 --> 01:38:20.640
我们专门为你安排几张桌子 建一个小团队
We'll give you a couple of desks, set up a small team, just for you.

01:38:20.720 --> 01:38:22.120
当然 科林也在附近
And of course Col's on hand.

01:38:23.200 --> 01:38:24.240
你怎么想？
What do you reckon?

01:38:25.240 --> 01:38:27.400
对了 我下周会雇用一个做声卡的
Oh, and hey, I'm hiring this sound chip guy next week,

01:38:27.480 --> 01:38:29.840
所以音乐我们可以解决 全都内部来做
so music we can take care of. All in-house.

01:38:30.360 --> 01:38:32.760
说吧 你怎么看？
So, come on. What's your answer?

01:38:35.480 --> 01:38:36.480
不
No.

01:38:42.720 --> 01:38:48.760
我的意思是 我确实想做你的游戏 但是…
I mean, yes, I want to do your game. I just... I just think I need to...

01:38:52.960 --> 01:38:56.240
我需要按自己想法来写
I need to write it how I know.

01:38:57.480 --> 01:38:59.720
就我一个人 在家里写
You know, just me. At home.

01:39:00.040 --> 01:39:02.280
在家里 你一个人？
At home. On your own?

01:39:02.880 --> 01:39:04.960
对 现在它全在我脑子里
Yeah, it's just that it's all in my head,

01:39:05.040 --> 01:39:06.320
如果让其他人插手
and I think if I let other people in, it'll just get, I don't know, stressy?

01:39:06.400 --> 01:39:09.200
可能会有点压力？

01:39:09.520 --> 01:39:11.360
“有点压力”？
"Stressy"?

01:39:11.800 --> 01:39:17.760
但我知道自己肯定能做好 对得起这本书
But I know that I can do it proper justice. The book.

01:39:18.360 --> 01:39:21.640
各种不同的故事线 平行现实
You know, divergent story paths. Parallel realities.

01:39:21.720 --> 01:39:24.400
-但它也只是个游戏吧？  -我明白
-It's still a game though, yeah?  -I get it.

01:39:25.120 --> 01:39:26.520
这小子是个匠人
The lad's a craftsman.

01:39:27.440 --> 01:39:29.280
孤独的林中居民 我也是
He's a lone woodsman. I'm the same.

01:39:29.360 --> 01:39:31.280
-可是…  -如我所说
-Yeah, but...  -It's like I say,

01:39:32.160 --> 01:39:33.920
团队适合做动作游戏
teams are fine for things like action titles,

01:39:34.000 --> 01:39:35.800
但涉及到玩概念的游戏
but when it's a concept piece,

01:39:36.640 --> 01:39:40.600
就需要一点点疯狂 最好是一个人来想
bit of madness is what you need and that works best when it's one mind.

01:39:40.880 --> 01:39:43.480
好了 蒂莫西·利里 我们晚点再议论《知觉之门》
Alright, Timothy Leary, we'll debate The Doors of Perception later--

01:39:43.560 --> 01:39:46.240
-那是赫胥黎的书 不是利里  -如果你要自己写
That was Huxley, not Leary. If you're going to write this on your tod,

01:39:46.320 --> 01:39:48.560
那重要的是 圣诞需要有成品
the important thing is putting it out for Christmas,

01:39:48.640 --> 01:39:51.040
所以9月12日前要编码完毕
so I'll need finished code by 12th September.

01:39:51.120 --> 01:39:53.000
-好 可以  -不能晚
-OK, sure.  -But no later.

01:40:01.640 --> 01:40:02.960
你都听些什么？
What do you listen to?

01:40:05.000 --> 01:40:06.480
以便让自己进入心流
To get in to the flow.

01:40:08.480 --> 01:40:09.720
音乐啊？
Oh, music?

01:40:12.760 --> 01:40:15.120
主要是合辑
Er, compilations mainly.

01:40:16.880 --> 01:40:17.960
拿支笔
Get a pen.

01:40:22.840 --> 01:40:24.800
我在解冻肉馅
I'm defrosting mince.

01:40:29.200 --> 01:40:31.600
这东西真是黑科技
It's like alien technology this thing.

01:40:32.800 --> 01:40:35.840
情况顺利吗？
Oh. How... how did it go?

01:40:37.760 --> 01:40:39.880
挺好的 很顺利
Good. Yeah, really good.

01:40:42.000 --> 01:40:43.080
他们收了
They're taking it.

01:40:43.320 --> 01:40:44.680
-太棒了  -是啊
Oh, well, that's great, isn't it?

01:40:46.680 --> 01:40:49.280
-很厉害  -你手上有肉汁
-Well done, mate.  -You've got mince juice on your hands.

01:40:51.000 --> 01:40:52.240
嗯
Yes.

01:40:55.080 --> 01:41:00.040
那是怎样安排？ 你去他们办公室还是？
So, how does it work then? Do you go into their office, or...?

01:41:00.120 --> 01:41:01.480
不去 我在这里写
No, I write it here.

01:41:02.480 --> 01:41:05.560
-自己一个人？  -嗯
-On your own?  -Yes.

01:41:09.760 --> 01:41:10.680
这个…
And...

01:41:11.760 --> 01:41:14.640
这种工作这样做好吗？
Is that the best way to work on something like this?

01:41:14.720 --> 01:41:16.240
为什么不好？
Why wouldn't it be?

01:41:16.520 --> 01:41:18.600
画面做得确实很厉害 罗宾
Well, the graphics are certainly impressive, Robin,

01:41:18.680 --> 01:41:21.760
但一个大问题是 玩起来怎么样？
but the big question is, what's it like to play?

01:41:21.840 --> 01:41:25.160
游戏玩法也一样很厉害
Well, the gameplay is just as impressive, I must say.

01:41:25.240 --> 01:41:27.680
这是科林·里特曼的游戏 所以大家期待不低
This is a Colin Ritman game, so we'd expect little else,

01:41:27.760 --> 01:41:31.560
但哪怕以他的标准来看 这游戏也确实非常好
but even by his standards this is really most impressive.

01:41:31.640 --> 01:41:34.400
游戏很有挑战 需要不断学习
It's challenging, there's quite a big learning curve,

01:41:34.480 --> 01:41:38.600
玩家会死很多次 必须多次尝试 但我并不怎么介意
so you die a lot and have to try again but I really didn't mind that much.

01:41:39.120 --> 01:41:41.680
听起来很棒 罗宾 你的评定是？
So it sounds great but what's your verdict, Robin?

01:41:41.760 --> 01:41:44.400
满分五星 我给四星 科林·里特曼再次成功了
Four stars out of five. Colin Ritman does it again.

01:41:44.800 --> 01:41:47.480
-所以还不够完美  -没有什么是完美无缺的
-So not quite perfect. -Well, nothing's perfect.

01:41:51.960 --> 01:41:54.480
我在那里 那边是科林·里特曼…
So there I am, there's Colin Ritman--

01:41:54.560 --> 01:41:57.960
“真正的科林·里特曼” 我记得你是这样说的
"The actual Colin Ritman," I believe you called him.

01:41:58.040 --> 01:42:03.680
没错 而且塔克尔先生给我机会
Yeah, exactly, and Mr. Thakur's offering me the chance to work there

01:42:03.760 --> 01:42:06.760
可以去他们办公室 在科林身边工作
in their own office alongside Colin.

01:42:08.760 --> 01:42:09.800
而我…
And I just...

01:42:11.240 --> 01:42:14.600
-不知道 有点太过…  -太过？
-I don't know. It was too...  -Too?

01:42:15.040 --> 01:42:16.440
太过理想 不像是真的
Good to be true.

01:42:18.600 --> 01:42:21.360
-我拒绝了  -你拒绝了？
-I said no.  -You said "no"?

01:42:21.920 --> 01:42:23.240
不是拒绝一整件事
Well, not to the whole thing,

01:42:23.320 --> 01:42:26.160
只是拒绝去那里工作 在其控制之下
just to working there and being under their control.

01:42:26.680 --> 01:42:27.640
不知道为什么
I don't know where it came from,

01:42:27.720 --> 01:42:29.920
我就说了“不” 然后必须给自己找理由
I just said "no" and then had to justify it

01:42:30.000 --> 01:42:32.360
说自己喜欢独自工作
by saying that I prefer to work alone.

01:42:33.960 --> 01:42:36.960
我只是不知道哪来的那股冲动
But I just don't know where the urge to say it came from.

01:42:37.720 --> 01:42:41.400
你听起来越来越自信了 这是好迹象
It sounds like you're growing in confidence. I think it's a good sign.

01:42:42.920 --> 01:42:45.360
他们还是让我做游戏 所以…
Well, they're still letting me do the game, so...

01:42:45.640 --> 01:42:49.680
做得好 斯蒂芬 太棒了
Well done, Stefan. That's great.

01:42:51.800 --> 01:42:53.080
你和我爸说的话一样
You sound like my dad.

01:42:58.040 --> 01:42:59.000
哦

01:43:01.440 --> 01:43:02.320
抱歉
Sorry.

01:43:03.920 --> 01:43:05.960
他有时会让我觉得很烦
He gets on my nerves sometimes.

01:43:06.480 --> 01:43:09.760
比如这个 我现在已经没事了
Like this... I'm fine now,

01:43:10.720 --> 01:43:14.560
我不懂为什么还要来参加这些治疗
I don't see why I need to keep coming to these sessions.

01:43:17.360 --> 01:43:20.720
我不知道 好像有种受到监控的感觉
It just feels like being, I don't know, monitored.

01:43:22.440 --> 01:43:26.760
也许是因为周年快到了 所以你有受到侵扰的感觉
Perhaps you're feeling intruded upon because of the anniversary looming.

01:43:27.720 --> 01:43:32.520
每年这段时间你都不好受 这点不能小看
It's a difficult time of year for you. We can't underestimate that.

01:43:34.040 --> 01:43:37.800
你想谈谈你母亲的遭遇吗？
Would you like to talk about what happened with your mother?

01:43:39.880 --> 01:43:45.880
回顾往事可能会有帮助 哪怕你觉得之前已经这样做过
It can be helpful to revisit things. Even if you feel you've done this before.

01:43:47.640 --> 01:43:50.760
你可能会有新的发现
You might discover something new.

01:44:20.040 --> 01:44:22.880
政府在你食物里下药 拍摄你
The government put drugs in your food and they film you.

01:44:40.720 --> 01:44:44.760
（三周后）

